	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hello and thanks in advance!
<br />
<br />I'm a plastics/composites fabricator, and an electronics beginner at best. I'm building a NES system into a thick glass case. I worry about the heat and I don't want to cut a bunch of cooling vents.
<br />
<br /> I want to add a 5v or 9v cooling fan.  Can I just solder the pos lead to the 5v pin on the board, and ground it?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
