		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />On my NES the 2A03 and PPU also get warm. The main inefficiency is the regulator itself, so you could avoid the issue by bypassing the whole mess and using a modern regulated power supply. There are also more modern regulators that dissipate less power. Finally, you might be able to use the glass case itself as a heat sink by thermally coupling the regulator with it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
